race.comment: JAM PACKED (3) gave away a considerable start over 1800m at Gold Coast last time before hitting the line well to finish fourth. Will drift back but is sure to prove tough to beat. VAN DE BAN (2) last start wound up strongly to finish second, beaten 2 lengths, over 1400m at Sunshine Coast. Will be tough to hold out again. The well-related WEEKEND ARTIST (11) (half to G3 winner and G2 placed I'm All The Talk) was prominent through the early and middle stages last time out before fading to finish fifth over 2200m at Gold Coast. Will appreciate the drop in grade. Well placed and is one of the contenders. CAPOCOLA (9) just missed the placings two runs back then did well last start but found one better over 1550m at Murwillumbah, beaten only 1.5 lengths. Finds a suitable race and can find the winner's circle.
